## Assessment of Your `Quadratic` Class

Your overall architecture is excellent — the class structure, constructor, all three getters and setters, `evaluate()`, `additiveInverse()`, and the discriminant formula are all correct. You clearly understand the mathematical concepts. However, there are **four bugs** to fix, two of them serious enough to cause wrong answers or crashes at runtime.

---

## ✅ What Is Correct

| Element | Status |
|---|---|
| Instance variables `a`, `b`, `c` | ✅ Correct |
| Constructor | ✅ Correct |
| `getA/B/C()` and `setA/B/C()` | ✅ Correct |
| `evaluate(double x)` | ✅ Correct |
