## Summary

| # | Where | What Went Wrong | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `getRoots()` two-root return | `/ 2*a` parsed as `÷2 × a` due to left-to-right precedence | Change to `/ (2*a)` |
| 2 | `getRoots()` no-roots return | `{null}` has length 1, collides with repeated-root case → NPE | Change to `{null, null}` |
| 3 | `factorize()` repeated-root branch | Returns size-1 array; spec requires two factors | Return two copies of the same factor |
| 4 | `factorize()` all real-root branches | Missing `a`; root passed directly instead of its negation | Use `new Linear(a, -a*r)` and `new Linear(1, -r)` |
